title: Did Trump try to ignore the attention of COVID-19's response by criticizing Obama to H1N1?
subtitle: Within one year of the first confirmed H1N1 case in the United States, more than 69 million people were injured, resulting in more than 12,000 deaths.
author: Madison Dapcevich
vclaim: US President Donald Trump tried to divert attention from his response to the COVID-19 epidemic by comparing it repeatedly with President Barack Obama's engagement with H1N1.
